2022-05-02T12:26:49: Flat V Weir station which accounts for various diverted waters. Replaced 69006 Bollin at Dunham Massey.
Flat V Weir with tapered downstream face. 11.6m wide B.S. This station replaces 69006 Bollin at Dunham Massey (750m downstream), which was closed as a flow station on 10/01/2002.

Flows contained and modular to bank full at 2m. Mill race on right bank has been present since the station was opened and takes approximately 10% of flow under low flow conditions. In 2009 a larinier fish pass was constructed on the left bank approximately 40m upstream of the station which takes approximately 25% of the flow at Q95.
The NRFA holds the combined record (main channel, mill race and fish pass), which has been produced since 19/11/2009. EA hold earlier data for the main channel.

Mixed geology but with extensive Drift cover (some Millstone Grit exposed in headwaters). Land use is very mixed - a predominantly rural catchment but with Macclesfield below the headwaters and other urban centres.
Very responsive regime. Reservoirs and many industrial abstractions and discharges affect low flows particularly.
